<br>
They've asked me for some advice regarding what types of items to buy in the bazaar and because I play a warrior, I thought I'd ask you all on the druid board.   <br>
<br>
Now for a Warrior the ranking, when you're looking to upgrade equipment, goes something like this:<br>
AC, HP's, STR, STA, DEX, AGI, MR, etc.<br>
<br>
But I'm just not sure what it would be for a Druid.  I'm guessing Wis &amp; Mana first/second and then maybe HP's and AC, but I'm not sure.  I'm also not sure of the Wis to Mana conversion rate.<br>
<br>
I'm also trying to create an value equivalency chart:<br>
1 Wis = ? mana = ? Hp's = ? Dex = ? Agi, etc.<br>
<br>
What I'm trying to get at is, if I were give you a choice - to offer you one point of wisdom OR a certain amount of mana, how much mana would I have to offer you to make you indifferent between the two choices?  <br>
Now how about 1 WIS or some HP's?<br>
or 1 WIS or some AC or other stats or resists?<br>
<br>
Why am I bothering with this?  Well it's a pain in the butt evaluating all the different items in the bazaar, and trying to decide what is better than what. Yes, some are obvious, but often it's not so easy.<br>
<br>
So I have a formula I use for my warrior which I've found is very valuable. When trying to choose between the different items I can buy I use this system.  I give one point for each of the following:<br>
Each point of AC, STR, DEX, STA, AGI gives me one point.  Every 5pts of HP, and Resists, gives me one point.<br>
<br>
So in effect for my warrior: <br>
1 AC = 5 HP = 1 STR = 1 DEX = 1 STA = 1 AGI = 5 Resist points<br>
(I don't give CHA, INT, or WIS any weight)<br>
So when comparing two items I use this system and add up the points on the two and compare. I'll usually buy the item that gives me more points for the price.<br>
<br>
Yes, I know the system is crude, and I'm sure I'll get a ton of critiques, or suggested modifications, but it seems to work ok. Give it a try. For example a Orc Fang Earring gets a score of 3AC+3STR+(15HP/5)=9 and a Bracelet of Might gets 12AC+15STR+(30Resist/5)=33<br>
<br>
I just want to get a sense of how a druid system might work and I'm not sure quite how the priority might sort out. It could be something like this:<br>
1Wis=5Mana=5STR=5HP's=5Dex=5STA=5AGI=5resists<br>
But then again, since I've never played a druid, I could be totally wrong.<br>
<br>
So what do you all think? Can you give me some sort of hierarchy for druid stats? And lastly, how do you rank the different stats that an item gives you?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Roos<br>
