<br>
How are your friends playing their druid?  Are they kiting and soloing or do they tend to be grouping druids?  Are they often grouped up with enchanters?  Are they at the level where they like to be the main healer or are they a mid/high lvl druid who's heals are mostly for patching in groups and they concentrate on dots/nukes/DS?<br>
<br>
Focus items can be more useful than stat items for druids who kite.  Extended Affliction, Affliction efficiency etc. will make mana for snares, roots, and dots more efficient.  If these druids do a lot of grouping, AC and HP may be more important because the group will be fighting a mob at close range and can mess up a druid who has relatively low HP and AC for priest classes.<br>
<br>
In sort, it really depends on how you play your class.  I tend to put things in the progression of mana&gt;wis&gt;AC&gt;HP&gt;STR (plate armor can get heavy)&gt;most other stats.<br>
<br>
